When using ss to determine listening sockets, you need to turn off name resolution. Whichoption should be passed to ss in order to disable name resolution?
A)  - n
B)  - x
C)  - a
D)  - r
A
A. The - n option disables name resolution, including hostnames and service names. Theother options shown are not relevant flags for this purpose.248Appendix  Answers to the Review Questions
